## Description {#details}

This file contains the declarations for metadata subclasses.

They represent the different flavors of metadata that live in LLVM.

<Link id="l00570" /><CodeLine lineNumber="570"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00571" /><CodeLine lineNumber="571"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// Transitional API for extracting constants from Metadata.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00572" /><CodeLine lineNumber="572"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00573" /><CodeLine lineNumber="573"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// This namespace contains transitional functions for metadata that points to</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00574" /><CodeLine lineNumber="574"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// \\a Constants.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00575" /><CodeLine lineNumber="575"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00576" /><CodeLine lineNumber="576"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// In prehistory -- when metadata was a subclass of \\a Value -- \\a MDNode</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00577" /><CodeLine lineNumber="577"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// operands could refer to any \\a Value.  There&#39;s was a lot of code like this:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00578" /><CodeLine lineNumber="578"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00579" /><CodeLine lineNumber="579"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// \\code</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00580" /><CodeLine lineNumber="580"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///     MDNode &#42;N = ...;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00581" /><CodeLine lineNumber="581"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///     auto &#42;CI = dyn&#95;cast&lt;ConstantInt&gt;(N-&gt;getOperand(2));</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00582" /><CodeLine lineNumber="582"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// \\endcode</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00583" /><CodeLine lineNumber="583"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00584" /><CodeLine lineNumber="584"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// Now that \\a Value and \\a Metadata are in separate hierarchies, maintaining</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00585" /><CodeLine lineNumber="585"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// the semantics for \\a isa(), \\a cast(), \\a dyn&#95;cast() (etc.) requires three</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00586" /><CodeLine lineNumber="586"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// steps: cast in the \\a Metadata hierarchy, extraction of the \\a Value, and</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00587" /><CodeLine lineNumber="587"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// cast in the \\a Value hierarchy.  Besides creating boiler-plate, this</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00588" /><CodeLine lineNumber="588"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// requires subtle control flow changes.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00589" /><CodeLine lineNumber="589"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00590" /><CodeLine lineNumber="590"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// The end-goal is to create a new type of metadata, called (e.g.) \\a MDInt,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00591" /><CodeLine lineNumber="591"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// so that metadata can refer to numbers without traversing a bridge to the \\a</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00592" /><CodeLine lineNumber="592"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// Value hierarchy.  In this final state, the code above would look like this:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00593" /><CodeLine lineNumber="593"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00594" /><CodeLine lineNumber="594"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// \\code</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00595" /><CodeLine lineNumber="595"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///     MDNode &#42;N = ...;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00596" /><CodeLine lineNumber="596"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///     auto &#42;MI = dyn&#95;cast&lt;MDInt&gt;(N-&gt;getOperand(2));</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00597" /><CodeLine lineNumber="597"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// \\endcode</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00598" /><CodeLine lineNumber="598"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00599" /><CodeLine lineNumber="599"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// The API in this namespace supports the transition.  \\a MDInt doesn&#39;t exist</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00600" /><CodeLine lineNumber="600"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// yet, and even once it does, changing each metadata schema to use it is its</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00601" /><CodeLine lineNumber="601"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// own mini-project.  In the meantime this API prevents us from introducing</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00602" /><CodeLine lineNumber="602"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// complex and bug-prone control flow that will disappear in the end.  In</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00603" /><CodeLine lineNumber="603"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// particular, the above code looks like this:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00604" /><CodeLine lineNumber="604"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00605" /><CodeLine lineNumber="605"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// \\code</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00606" /><CodeLine lineNumber="606"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///     MDNode &#42;N = ...;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00607" /><CodeLine lineNumber="607"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///     auto &#42;CI = mdconst::dyn&#95;extract&lt;ConstantInt&gt;(N-&gt;getOperand(2));</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00608" /><CodeLine lineNumber="608"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// \\endcode</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00609" /><CodeLine lineNumber="609"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00610" /><CodeLine lineNumber="610"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// The full set of provided functions includes:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00611" /><CodeLine lineNumber="611"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00612" /><CodeLine lineNumber="612"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   mdconst::hasa                &lt;=&gt; isa</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00613" /><CodeLine lineNumber="613"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   mdconst::extract             &lt;=&gt; cast</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00614" /><CodeLine lineNumber="614"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   mdconst::extract&#95;or&#95;null     &lt;=&gt; cast&#95;or&#95;null</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00615" /><CodeLine lineNumber="615"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   mdconst::dyn&#95;extract         &lt;=&gt; dyn&#95;cast</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00616" /><CodeLine lineNumber="616"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   mdconst::dyn&#95;extract&#95;or&#95;null &lt;=&gt; dyn&#95;cast&#95;or&#95;null</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00617" /><CodeLine lineNumber="617"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00618" /><CodeLine lineNumber="618"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// The target of the cast must be a subclass of \\a Constant.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00619" /><CodeLine lineNumber="619" lineLink="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/mdconst"><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">namespace </span><span class="doxyHighlight"><a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/mdconst">mdconst</a> &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00620" /><CodeLine lineNumber="620"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00621" /><CodeLine lineNumber="621" lineLink="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/mdconst/detail"><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">namespace </span><span class="doxyHighlight"><a href="/docs/api/namespaces/detail">detail</a> &#123;</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l01049" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1049"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01050" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1050"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// Metadata node.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01051" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1051"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01052" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1052"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// Metadata nodes can be uniqued, like constants, or distinct.  Temporary</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01053" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1053"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// metadata nodes (with full support for RAUW) can be used to delay uniquing</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01054" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1054"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// until forward references are known.  The basic metadata node is an \\a</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01055" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1055"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// MDTuple.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01056" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1056"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01057" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1057"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// There is limited support for RAUW at construction time.  At construction</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01058" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1058"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// time, if any operand is a temporary node (or an unresolved uniqued node,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01059" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1059"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// which indicates a transitive temporary operand), the node itself will be</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01060" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1060"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// unresolved.  As soon as all operands become resolved, it will drop RAUW</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01061" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1061"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// support permanently.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01062" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1062"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01063" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1063"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// If an unresolved node is part of a cycle, \\a resolveCycles() needs</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01064" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1064"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// to be called on some member of the cycle once all temporary nodes have been</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01065" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1065"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// replaced.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01066" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1066"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01067" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1067"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// MDNodes can be large or small, as well as resizable or non-resizable.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01068" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1068"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// Large MDNodes&#39; operands are allocated in a separate storage vector,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01069" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1069"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// whereas small MDNodes&#39; operands are co-allocated. Distinct and temporary</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01070" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1070"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// MDnodes are resizable, but only MDTuples support this capability.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01071" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1071"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l01677" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1677"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// Placeholder metadata for operands of distinct MDNodes.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01678" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1678"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01679" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1679"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// This is a lightweight placeholder for an operand of a distinct node.  It&#39;s</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01680" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1680"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// purpose is to help track forward references when creating a distinct node.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01681" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1681"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// This allows distinct nodes involved in a cycle to be constructed before</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01682" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1682"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// their operands without requiring a heavyweight temporary node with</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01683" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1683"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// full-blown RAUW support.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01684" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1684"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01685" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1685"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// Each placeholder supports only a single MDNode user.  Clients should pass</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01686" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1686"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// an ID, retrieved via \\a getID(), to indicate the &quot;real&quot; operand that this</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01687" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1687"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// should be replaced with.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01688" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1688"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01689" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1689"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// While it would be possible to implement move operators, they would be</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01690" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1690"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// fairly expensive.  Leave them unimplemented to discourage their use</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01691" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1691"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// (clients can use std::deque, std::list, BumpPtrAllocator, etc.).</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01692" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1692" lineLink="/docs/api/classes/llvm/distinctmdoperandplaceholder"><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">class </span><span class="doxyHighlight"><a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/distinctmdoperandplaceholder/#af6749770ad338c5719e1f3602bd8b5ea">DistinctMDOperandPlaceholder</a> : </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">public</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/metadata/#ac265aa582f1e66e4e45d6a964b9bd303">Metadata</a> &#123;</span></CodeLine>
